Because of the prefix Open- on its name, OpenSSL is often associated with [[OpenBSD]]; which distributes several programs using the naming style of Open*, like [[OpenSSH]]. This is however a mistake as OpenSSL is developed completely outside of the scope of OpenBSD by The OpenSSL Project, under a different license than is commonly used by OpenBSD. Because of the prefix Open- on its name, OpenSSL is often associated with [[OpenBSD]] {{fact}}; which distributes several programs using the naming style of Open*, like [[OpenSSH]]. This is however a mistake as OpenSSL is developed completely outside of the scope of OpenBSD by The OpenSSL Project, under a different license than is commonly used by OpenBSD. Like with [[FreeBSD]]'s [[OpenBSM]], the project simply shares the goal of having an open source implementation of a valuable asset for the common good.
